{"word":"φρόνιμος","slug":"φρόνιμος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>φρόνιμος, ον</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:φρήν\">φρήν</a></el>] ‘using one’s wits effectivly’, <b>prudent, judicious <a href='B:470 7:24'>Mt 7:24</a>; <a href='B:470 10:16'>10:16</a>; <a href='B:470 25:2'>25:2</a>; <a href='B:490 12:42'>Lk 12:42</a>; <a href='B:490 16:8'>16:8</a>; <a href='B:530 4:10'>1 Cor 4:10</a>; <a href='B:530 10:15'>10:15</a>;</b> in satire <b><a href='B:540 11:19'>2 Cor 11:19</a>.</b> <el>γίνεσϑε φρόνιμοι <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ὡς\">ὡς</a> οἱ ὄφεις</el> be smart as snakes = be snakewise; <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἐν\">ἐν</a></el> (<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:παρά\">παρά</a></el>) <el>ἑαυτοῖς φρόνιμοι</el> wise from your own point of view = thinking yourselves so wise <b><a href='B:520 11:25'>Ro 11:25</a>; <a href='B:520 12:16'>12:16</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:φρόνησις\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:φρονίμως\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}